cs.IT, cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.DS, cs.NA. 

The paper proposes a new wavelet transform applicable to functions defined on high dimensional data, weighted graphs, and networks. This suggests that the paper could belong to several sub-categories, including Information Theory (cs.IT) due to the focus on signal processing and data compression, Machine Learning (cs.LG) due to the use of adaptive orthonormal wavelets, Computer Vision (cs.CV) due to the application of the proposed transform to image denoising, Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) due to the use of a hierarchical tree structure, and Numerical Analysis (cs.NA) due to the use of filtering and decimation schemes.
